==Relation to other polynomials==

q-Hahn polynomials→    [[Quantum q-Krawtchouk polynomials]]：

<math>\lim_{a \to \infty}Q_{n}(q^-{x};a;p,N|q)=K_{n}^{qtm}(q^-{x};p,N;q)</math>

q-Hahn polynomials→  [[Hahn polynomials]]

make the substitution<math>\alpha=q^{\alpha}</math>,<math>\beta=q^{\beta}</math> into definition of q-Hahn polynomials, and find the limit q→1, we obtain

：
<math>_3F_2([-n, \alpha+\beta+n+1, -x], [\alpha+1, -N], 1)</math>，which is exactly [[Hahn polynomials]].

